PROJECT CONTEXT

We are building an **AI Second Brain / Personal Knowledge Manager** using a **multi-agent architecture**.

The system should:

• Accept knowledge sources (PDFs, notes, transcripts, bookmarks)
• Extract and store knowledge
• Organize information into structured topics
• Generate actionable outputs such as summaries, flashcards, quizzes, and study plans
• Maintain long-term knowledge memory
• Execute tasks such as scheduling revisions or creating actionable learning plans

The system uses three cooperating agents:

Planner Agent
Decides strategy, topic structure, and task planning.

Retriever Agent
Extracts knowledge from documents and retrieves relevant context using embeddings and vector search.

Executor Agent
Generates outputs and performs actions such as creating study plans, flashcards, quizzes, and schedules.

